        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks for Francis Darwin’s <hi rend="italic">Dipsacus</hi> paper.</p> 
            <p>Dislikes the word "protoplasm", because improved microscopes will uncover more fundamental substances. Also "plasma" merely hides the ignorance of modern chemists.</p>
            <p>Expects waxy, glaucous-leaved plants to be most frequent in dry temperate climates.</p>
        </abstract>
